Nematocysts of two categories were observed in this hydroid (
Fig. 15
). They were identified as A-type b-mastigophores (7.1–8.0 long x 2.0–2.3 μm wide, undischarged, n=10, ROMIZ B4420) and B-type b-mastigophores (13.5–14.8 long x 2.8–4.0 μm wide, undischarged, n=10, ROMIZ B4420).

